      • setCompensation

        public void setCompensation(long prevCumulatedDuration,
                   int nbPrevious)
        Sets the duration compensation of this window. This allows this window to have a longer duration than the maximum if the previous windows are shorter, and vice-versa.
        Parameters:
        prevCumulatedDuration - The cumulated duration of the previous windows.
        nbPrevious - The number of previous windows.

      • add

        public void add(LinkedList<Sample> linesToAdd)
        Adds the specified samples of values to this group.
        Parameters:
        linesToAdd - The Samples to add, in the order they should be added to this window. This list will be cleared and receive the oldest samples in this group that do not fit anymore in the maximum length. The oldest of these samples is added first in the list, the newest is added last.

      • getDuration

        public long getDuration()
        Returns the current duration of this window in milliseconds. This corresponds to the actual sum of the durations of all the samples contained in this window, not to the desired duration.
        Returns:
        the duration of this window.

      • trimBeginningToReach

      • trimBeginning

        public void trimBeginning(long millisToSkip)
        Removes the oldest (first) samples from this window. This window's duration is shortened by millisToStop milliseconds.
        Parameters:
        millisToSkip - The amount of time that has to be cut from this window.
